# UI Components Guidelines

## Component Architecture

### Base Components
The project uses a component library based on [shadcn/ui](mdc:https:/ui.shadcn.com) with a custom "new-york" style. Base components are located in [components/ui/](mdc:components/ui).

### Component Categories
1. **Layout Components**
   - [Sidebar](mdc:components/ui/sidebar.tsx)
   - [Sheet](mdc:components/ui/sheet.tsx)
   - [Drawer](mdc:components/ui/drawer.tsx)
   - [Card](mdc:components/ui/card.tsx)

2. **Form Components**
   - [Input](mdc:components/ui/input.tsx)
   - [Textarea](mdc:components/ui/textarea.tsx)
   - [Select](mdc:components/ui/select.tsx)
   - [Checkbox](mdc:components/ui/checkbox.tsx)
   - [Radio Group](mdc:components/ui/radio-group.tsx)
   - [Switch](mdc:components/ui/switch.tsx)

3. **Navigation Components**
   - [Breadcrumb](mdc:components/ui/breadcrumb.tsx)
   - [Navigation Menu](mdc:components/ui/navigation-menu.tsx)
   - [Tabs](mdc:components/ui/tabs.tsx)
   - [Menubar](mdc:components/ui/menubar.tsx)

4. **Feedback Components**
   - [Alert](mdc:components/ui/alert.tsx)
   - [Toast](mdc:components/ui/toast.tsx)
   - [Progress](mdc:components/ui/progress.tsx)
   - [Skeleton](mdc:components/ui/skeleton.tsx)

5. **Overlay Components**
   - [Dialog](mdc:components/ui/dialog.tsx)
   - [Popover](mdc:components/ui/popover.tsx)
   - [Tooltip](mdc:components/ui/tooltip.tsx)
   - [Hover Card](mdc:components/ui/hover-card.tsx)

## Component Guidelines

### 1. Component Structure
```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
import { ComponentProps } from "@/components/ui/component"

interface ComponentProps {
  className?: string
  // other props
}

export function Component({ className, ...props }: ComponentProps) {
  return (
    <div className={cn("base-styles", className)} {...props}>
      {/* component content */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

### 2. Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow the project's color scheme defined in [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js)
- Use CSS variables for theming
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use the `cn()` utility for conditional class names

### 3. Component Composition
- Keep components small and focused
- Use composition over inheritance
- Follow the single responsibility principle
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Implement proper prop validation

### 4. Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Implement proper ARIA attributes
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Maintain proper color contrast
- Support screen readers

### 5. Performance
- Use React.memo when appropriate
- Implement proper loading states
- Use proper image optimization
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use proper code splitting

## Best Practices

### 1. Component Organization
- Keep related components together
- Use proper file naming (kebab-case)
- Export components from index files
- Keep component files focused

### 2. Props Management
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Provide default values when appropriate
- Document complex props
- Use proper prop validation

### 3. State Management
- Use local state for component-specific state
- Use context for shared state
- Use proper state management patterns
- Implement proper loading states

### 4. Error Handling
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Show user-friendly error messages
- Handle edge cases gracefully
- Provide fallback UI

### 5. Testing
- Write unit tests for components
- Test accessibility
- Test responsive behavior
- Test edge cases

## Common Patterns

### 1. Form Components
```tsx
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form"
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod"
import * as z from "zod"

const formSchema = z.object({
  // schema definition
})

export function FormComponent() {
  const form = useForm({
    resolver: zodResolver(formSchema)
  })
  
  return (
    <Form {...form}>
      {/* form fields */}
    </Form>
  )
}
```

### 2. Dialog Components
```tsx
import {
  Dialog,
  DialogContent,
  DialogHeader,
  DialogTitle,
} from "@/components/ui/dialog"

export function DialogComponent() {
  return (
    <Dialog>
      <DialogHeader>
        <DialogTitle>Title</DialogTitle>
      </DialogHeader>
      <DialogContent>
        {/* content */}
      </DialogContent>
    </Dialog>
  )
}
```

### 3. Loading States
```tsx
import { Skeleton } from "@/components/ui/skeleton"

export function LoadingComponent() {
  return (
    <div className="space-y-4">
      <Skeleton className="h-4 w-[250px]" />
      <Skeleton className="h-4 w-[200px]" />
    </div>
  )
}
```

